This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it focuses on word embeddings and their ability to capture semantic information. The use of probability densities is a common technique in natural language processing, and the paper specifically mentions the WordNet hypernym relationship prediction task and the HyperLex lexical entailment dataset, which are both commonly used in natural language processing research. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), or neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on natural language processing and the specific tasks mentioned, it is more likely to belong to cs.CL than any of these other sub-categories.
